                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51843",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avincent",
                        "name": "avincent",
                        "displayName": "Ashleigh Vincent",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Now 6 years old. \r\n\r\nPlease bump this as it is not minor. The main reason to create a PDF instead of just serving HTML is in order lock the document so it cannot be edited by the recipient. \r\n\r\nI know you are all concentrating on ZF2 now but it is going to be at least another 2 years before that is trustworthy enough to use in a commercial project. Please try and backport any PDF locking or encryption into  ZF1 too.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=avincent",
                        "name": "avincent",
                        "displayName": "Ashleigh Vincent",
                        "active": true
